>>13571232
t. Doesn't know how to google. 
It's fairly easy. 
>Download and install OBS
https://obsproject.com/
Don't worry too much about a stream configuration, you'll just need the recording feature for this.
>Go to the "Sources" box. Click on the + icon. Select the "Navegador" or web source. 
>Paste the URL to the source, but you should stretch the red square to fit the horizontal sides of the black rectangle.
>When the video is running, you can't interact with it on the OBS screen, but there will be a tab that says "interact" or something like that. Use that to skip ads, activate full screen, etc.
>Select "comenzar grabación" after the ad, there will usually be ads through a stream, but don't pause the recording, just skip it. 
>When the recording is over just select "detener grabacion"
There probably are faster or better ways to get this done but this is the way I do it.
Keep in mind:
>DONT have the stream running on your own browser and the obs browser source at the same time. 
>Disable the mic/aux audio input by muting it, simply click the audio symbol to disable it. If you don't outside audio sources will be picked up.
